cc:Work.dc:title: Elvie #010
cc:Work.dc:description:
[Panel 1: Outside a Primary School. Elvie's voice emanates from one of the windows] Elvie: My niece tells me that she's got a new teacher who used to work for Microsoft.
[Panel 2: Inside the headmaster's office] Elvie: I hope he won't be teaching the kids that computing starts and ends with Word and Excel.
[Panel 3] Headmaster: I think you've misunderstood -- he's not an I.T. teacher -- he's teaching maths.
[Panel 4: In the classroom the teacher is talking to Elvie's niece] Teacher: Now Jessica, what number comes after eight? Jessica: Nine, sir?
[Panel 5] Teacher: No, no, no. Don't you remember what I taught you about the 'Number Line'? [The blackboard behind them reveals that the number line runs as follows: 1, 2, 3, 95, 98, ME, XP, Vista, 7, 8, 10 - with arrows indicating the location of the "decimals", 3.1 and 8.1]
